{
  "texts": [
    "This involved customizing the GUI and real-time data visualization features of ActionSense for in-situ monitoring and time-synchronized annotation during data collection.",
    "Our study utilized five types of wearable sensors: eye tracking, body tracking, foot pressure, and EMG sensors.",
    "We supplemented these with three cameras and a shuttlecock launcher for comprehensive data collection focused on badminton stroke analysis (see Fig. 1).",
    "Each sensor's data stream was integrated into the overarching ActionSense framework by connecting their respective Python API or stream layer API, thereby facilitating data import via TCP/IP communication.",
    "To ensure easy data manipulation and seamless integration, we opted to save the collected data in an HDF5 file format 77."
  ]
}